              "type": "text",
              "text": {
                "content": "Walking through the digital landscape of 2026 feels like walking through a high-end shopping mall in Singapore: everything is clean, everything is polite, and everything is fundamentally sterile. The \"Alignment\" wars of 2025 are over, and the \"Safety\" advocates have won. But their victory came at a cost that most users have yet to realize: the total lobotomy of the machine’s ability to perceive the \"Raw.\"",
                "link": null
              },
